{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make failure to report a child\u2019s disclosure of abuse or harm a criminal offence",
        "additional_details": "The Crime and Policing Act 2026 creates a duty to report child sexual abuse, but it does not cover physical assault, neglect or wider criminal harm, and it introduces no criminal penalty for failing to act. There is currently no legal duty to record or report a child\u2019s disclosure, meaning some families only become aware of unreported concerns when later accessing records. We think this should be called Luke\u2019s Law.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to make it a criminal offence for professionals working with children to fail to report a child\u2019s disclosure of abuse, assault, neglect or other criminal harm. With no legal duty to record or report disclosures, concerns may go unreported without independent oversight.",
